Template: nightwatcher-ingest/incoming
Type: string
Default: /astronomy/astro-imaging/incoming
Description: Directory to watch for incoming FITS frames:
 The watcher scans this directory (recursively) for new FITS files to classify,
 rename, and file into the archive tree. Point your capture applications here.

Template: nightwatcher-ingest/enable_sqm
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Stamp frames with a sky-brightness (SQM) reading?
 If enabled, each light frame is stamped with the nearest reading from the
 NightWatcher database. Requires the database password below, and a matching
 site entry in /etc/nwingest/nwingest.yaml.

Template: nightwatcher-ingest/enable_extension
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Show a NightWatcher2 web-UI "Ingest" tab while running?
 If enabled, the watcher registers with NightWatcher2 so a tab shows its live
 activity. Requires the database password below.

Template: nightwatcher-ingest/db_password
Type: password
Description: NightWatcher database password:
 Needed only for the SQM stamp and the web-UI tab. Leave blank to skip the
 database features for now; you can set it later with:
 dpkg-reconfigure nightwatcher-ingest

Template: nightwatcher-ingest/archive_group
Type: string
Description: Group to grant the "nwingest" service account (optional):
 The service runs as the unprivileged "nwingest" user, which needs read access
 to the incoming directory and write access to the archive tree. If those are
 group-accessible, name that group to add nwingest to it. Leave blank to arrange
 access yourself (e.g. directory ownership or a filesystem ACL).
